## 🚀 Installation

1. Clone this repository.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Smart-Helmet-System.git
```

2. Open the Arduino code in Arduino IDE.

3. Install required libraries:
   - TinyGPS++
   - SoftwareSerial
   - Wire
   - Adafruit MPU6050 (if using MPU6050)

4. Select the correct board and COM port.

5. Upload the code to the Arduino/ESP32.

---

## 📱 Output

- Helmet not worn → Ignition OFF
- Alcohol detected → Ignition OFF + Buzzer ON
- Safe condition → Vehicle starts
- Accident detected → SMS sent with GPS coordinates

Example SMS:

```
Emergency Alert!

Accident Detected.

Location:
https://maps.google.com/?q=12.9716,77.5946

Please reach immediately.
```

